   674	
   675	3\.05\.02 Current State Process
   676	
   677	Pivot currently processes standalone expense vendor bills manually\. When expense invoices arrive \(utilities, rent, insurance, etc\.\), the AP team must:
   678	
   679	1. Receive invoice in email
   680	2. Forward to manager \(e\.g\., Ken\) for approval
   681	3. Wait for approval response
   682	4. Manually enter bill into system
   683	5. Mark as approved and post
   684	
   685	This process is cumbersome, creates delays, and risks bills being forgotten in hold status awaiting approval\.
   686	
   687	__Current State Challenges:__
   688	
   689	- Manual entry of standalone expense vendor bills
   690	- Email\-based approval process is inefficient
   691	- Risk of forgetting bills in hold status
   692	- Time\-consuming for routine expense invoices
   693	- No automated tracking or follow\-up
   694	
   695	__User Story:__
   696	
   697	- As an AP Manager, I need automated processing for standalone expense invoices so that we can eliminate manual entry, streamline approvals, and reduce the risk of missing bills\.
   698	
   699	3\.05\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
   700	
   701	Pivot requires accommodation through custom AP automation workflow for standalone expense vendor bills\. This custom solution will be scoped for Phase 1 inclusion, pending timeline and budget analysis\. Pending decision based on offered solutions\.
   702	
   703	__Email\-to\-Vendor\-Bill Automation:__
   704	A dedicated email inbox will be configured for expense invoice forwarding\. When invoices are received at this inbox, automated processing will:
   705	
   706	1. Extract invoice data from PDF attachments
   707	2. This requirement can be met using NetSuite’s native allocation functionality\.
   708	3. Attach PDF to vendor bill record
   709	4. Route requests the appropriate approver based on predefined rules\. Reminders or saved searches can be used to support this process\.
   710	
   711	__Technical Approach:__
   712	The custom automation will leverage NetSuite's email integration framework to monitor the dedicated inbox and extract vendor, amount, date, and GL account information from PDF attachments\. Automated workflows will create vendor bill records with proper approval routing based on configurable thresholds and GL account classifications\. The solution will include exception handling for invoices that cannot be parsed automatically, routing them to a manual review queue\.
   713	
   714	__Automated Approval Workflow:__
   715	Auto\-created vendor bills will be placed in unapproved state and routed through configurable approval workflows\. Approvers will receive notifications, can review bills with attached PDFs in NetSuite Orion, and approve/reject directly in the system\. Upon approval, bills post automatically to GL\. This eliminates the manual email\-based approval process and ensures bills are tracked in the system from receipt through payment\.
   716	
   717	__Phase 1 Inclusion Decision:__
   718	The AP automation solution requires custom development and integration effort\. GSI will provide timeline and hour impact analysis to determine feasibility of Phase 1 inclusion\. If scope or budget constraints necessitate deferral, this functionality can be implemented in Phase 2 while using standard manual bill entry processes in Phase 1\.
   719	
   720	__Future Phase: Vendor Invoice Follow\-Up:__
   721	Automated vendor invoice follow\-up capability \(tracking expected invoices, sending reminders to vendors\) is acknowledged as a valuable future enhancement but is planned for Phase 2 or Phase 3 implementation\.
   722	
