  1328	3\.10\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
  1329	
  1330	NetSuite Orion provides standard CSV import functionality for journal entries\. GSI will work with Pivot to review the current UKG export template and create a NetSuite Orion CSV import map that replicates and improves upon the current D365 import process\. NetSuite calls this a "CSV import map" \- a configuration tool that defines how UKG's payroll journal entry export format maps to NetSuite's journal entry import format\.
  1331	
  1332	__CSV Import Map Configuration:__
  1333	GSI will review Pivot's current UKG template to understand the data structure and any transformations currently being performed \(including macros if present\)\. The NetSuite Orion CSV import map will be configured to:
  1334	
  1335	- Map column mappings \(UKG field → NetSuite field\)
  1336	- Map account mappings \(UKG accounts → NetSuite COA\)
  1337	- Handle data transformations \(date formats, number formats, etc\.\)
  1338	- Configure department allocation and tagging
  1339	- Set up validation rules to catch errors before import
  1340	- Replicate any current template logic or macros in NetSuite's import mapping
  1341	
  1342	__Import Process:__
  1343	Once the CSV import map is configured, importing payroll journal entries becomes a simple, repeatable process that mirrors Pivot's current workflow:
  1344	
  1345	1. Export payroll journal entry from UKG in CSV format \(same as current process\)
  1346	2. Upload CSV file to NetSuite
  1347	3. Select UKG Payroll CSV import map
  1348	4. Review validation results and error reports
  1349	5. Process import to create journal entries automatically
  1350	6. Review imported journal entries before posting
  1351	
  1352	This standard NetSuite Orion functionality requires no custom development, only configuration of the import map to match UKG's data format\. GSI will work with Connie to ensure the NetSuite Orion import map handles all current template requirements including department tagging and any data transformations currently performed manually or through macros\.
