  1842	## <a id="_Toc214912001"></a>__3\.15 Vendor Management__
  1843	
  1844	3\.15\.01 Your Business Requirements
  1845	
  1846	- __REQ\-3\.15\.01__: Comprehensive vendor return authorization process \(ACCOMMODATE\)
  1847	- __REQ\-3\.15\.02__: FedEx integration for vendor returns \(ALIGNS\)
  1848	
  1849	3\.15\.02 Current State Process
  1850	
  1851	Pivot does not currently process vendor return authorizations \(VRAs\) in their system\. This functionality is needed in the new system to properly track vendor returns, manage return authorization workflows, and integrate with FedEx shipping for return shipments\.
  1852	
  1853	__Current State:__
  1854	
  1855	- Vendor returns processed manually outside system
  1856	- No VRA tracking or workflow in current system
  1857	- Want to implement VRA in new system\. After VRA is marked as approve by vendor, it will generate a credit memo that will math the correspondent AP transaction
  1858	- Need FedEx integration for return shipping
  1859	
  1860	__User Story:__
  1861	
  1862	- As a Warehouse Manager, I need a comprehensive VRA process in the system so that we can track vendor returns, manage credits, and integrate shipping\.
  1863	
  1864	3\.15\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
  1865	
  1866	NetSuite/Orion provides standard Vendor Return Authorization \(VRA\) functionality with integrated shipping capabilities\. The VRA process will require custom configuration and a dedicated discovery session with warehouse personnel to define detailed requirements\.
  1867	
  1868	__Standard VRA Functionality:__
  1869	
  1870	NetSuite Orion includes built\-in VRA capabilities that:
  1871	
  1872	- Create VRA records linked to original purchase orders
  1873	- Track return quantities and reasons
  1874	- Generate return packing slips
  1875	- Link to vendor credits when credits are received
  1876	- Provide VRA reporting and tracking
  1877	
  1878	__Approval Workflow:__
  1879	The standard VRA process includes an optional approval workflow\. GSI recommends bypassing the approval requirement since the warehouse manager creating the VRA likely has authority to execute returns\. This streamlines the process while maintaining tracking and audit trail\.
  1880	
  1881	__FedEx Integration:__
  1882	NetSuite provides standard FedEx integration for shipping, including return shipments\. The integration supports multiple FedEx accounts per warehouse location \(REQ\-3\.03\.04\), enabling proper cost allocation across Pivot's multi\-location operations\. When creating VRAs, users can generate FedEx return labels directly from NetSuite Orion\.
  1883	
  1884	__Warehouse Session Required:__
  1885	A dedicated discovery session with Marie Guerrero, Brian Hagerty, Brad, and Sandra Rudloff is needed to define detailed VRA requirements including:
  1886	
  1887	- VRA creation workflow
  1888	- Return reason codes
  1889	- Disposition tracking
  1890	- Credit processing workflow
  1891	- Receiving process for returned items
  1892	- Integration with inventory management
  1893	
  1894	3\.15\.04 Future State Process
  1895	
  1896	1. __VRA Creation__:
  1897		- Warehouse identifies need for vendor return
  1898		- Create VRA record in NetSuite linked to PO
  1899		- Specify return quantities and reason codes
  1900		- Generate return packing slip
  1901	2. __Shipping__:
  1902		- Create FedEx return shipment from VRA
  1903		- Generate and print return label
  1904		- Ship return to vendor
  1905		- Tracking number captured in VRA record
  1906	3. __Credit Processing__:
  1907		- Receive vendor credit
  1908		- Link credit to VRA record
  1909		- Update status to complete
  1910		- Close VRA
