    55	## Executive Summary
    56	
    57	KB+Hoag, formed through the merger of KB and Hoag operations, requires a modern, integrated financial management solution to replace their current system built on NetSuite Core. The organization currently operates with significant manual processes, a large and unwieldy chart of accounts (40+ pages), and a 10-day accounting close cycle that relies on Excel-based workflows.
    58	
    59	The proven Orion/NetSuite Financial Management solution directly addresses these operational challenges by providing:
    60	
    61	- **Integrated financial management** across accounting, banking, accounts payable/receivable, and reporting
    62	- **Automated processes** that eliminate manual steps in payment processing, expense management, and financial reporting
    63	- **Real-time visibility** into project profitability, cash flow, and financial metrics through consolidated dashboards
    64	- **Streamlined period close** with guided checklists and automated processes, reducing close time from 10 days to an estimated 5-7 days
    65	- **Proven capabilities** used by similar furniture dealerships to manage complex project-based accounting
    66	
    67	**Implementation Status**: The organization has completed comprehensive discovery sessions identifying 38 specific requirements. Of these:
    68	- **26 requirements (68%)** align with standard Orion/NetSuite functionality
    69	- **9 requirements (24%)** require business process adaptation
    70	- **3-5 requirements (16%)** will need custom solution design (pending strategic decisions)
    71	
    72	**Critical Path Items**: Eight follow-up discovery sessions have been identified to finalize requirements before configuration. Three strategic decisions must be completed before detailed design can proceed, as they will significantly impact scope, custom development needs, and implementation timeline.
    73	
