   869	
   870	#### Your Business Requirements
   871	
   872	**REQ-023:** Determine if 15% labor markup (contingency line) will continue in NetSuite (ADAPT - DECISION PENDING)
   873	- Current practice in Core adds 15% contingency to labor costs
   874	- Evidence: "That may be up for debate as to whether or not we would want to keep that... Matt and Mark decision... Commission is paid on that..." - Kipp
   875	- **CRITICAL DECISION REQUIRED**: Leadership decision impacts commission structure, custom development scope, and financial reporting
   876	- Session Dependency: **SESSION 3 REQUIRED** - Cannot proceed without final decision
   877	- Implementation Impact: If continued, may require custom script development; if eliminated, requires sales communication
   878	
   879	**REQ-024:** Maintain separate Project GP vs. Commissionable GP reporting and KPIs (ACCOMMODATE - DECISION DEPENDENT)
   880	- Two distinct GP metrics for different audiences: true project profitability vs. commission-eligible earnings
   881	- Evidence: "That's why we have two... different set of KPIs... So, we have a set of KPIs for project gross profit, and then we have commissionable gross profit" - Kipp
   882	- Complexity: Requires custom reporting, dashboards, and role-based visibility
   883	- Dependent on: REQ-023 (labor markup decision) and REQ-025 (role-based permissions)
   884	
   885	**REQ-025:** Configure role-based permissions for different GP visibility (ACCOMMODATE - DECISION DEPENDENT)
   886	- Sales team sees Commissionable GP; Management sees true Project GP
   887	- Evidence: "Permission Control: Different people see different KPIs... Role-based visibility... Sales may see commissionable GP... Management sees true project GP" - Discussion
   888	- Complexity: Permission design must be tested and validated
   889	- Dependent on: REQ-023 and REQ-024 decisions
   890	
   891	#### Current State Process
   892	
   893	KB+Hoag's current commission structure includes a 15% contingency markup on labor costs. This markup:
   894	- Adds 15% to labor line items before calculating commissions
   895	- Affects commission calculations (commission is paid on the markup as well as base labor)
   896	- Creates a difference between Project GP (actual cost-based) and Commissionable GP (cost + markup)
   897	
   898	Sales teams see Commissionable GP (which includes the 15% markup) for commission purposes. Management sees true Project GP (without markup) for actual profitability analysis.
   899	
   900	#### Orion/NetSuite Solution
   901	
   902	Orion/NetSuite enables both approaches through flexible project accounting and reporting capabilities:
   903	
   904	**Option A: Continue 15% Labor Markup**
   905	If leadership decides to continue the 15% markup, custom script development can automate the calculation at order line-item level. The markup would be calculated and added to labor costs automatically. Commission rules would be configured to apply commissions to the total (base labor + markup). Project GP and Commissionable GP would be tracked separately through distinct custom fields and calculated values.
   906	
   907	**Option B: Eliminate 15% Labor Markup**
   908	If leadership decides to eliminate the markup, all labor costs would be charged at actual cost. Commissions would be based on actual project costs only. Project GP and Commissionable GP would converge (or the distinction could be eliminated entirely). Sales team would need clear communication about the impact on commission calculations.
   909	
   910	Both options require SESSION 3 detailed discussion and final leadership decision before custom development can proceed.
   911	
   912	#### Future State Process
   913	
   914	**If 15% Markup Continues:**
   915	At order line-item entry, labor costs are entered. The system automatically calculates and applies the 15% markup, creating a total labor line value. Commission calculations apply commissions to this total (base + markup). At project completion, the system generates two reporting views: Project GP (actual cost) and Commissionable GP (cost + markup). Sales teams access dashboards showing Commissionable GP. Management accesses dashboards showing true Project GP for actual profitability analysis.
   916	
   917	**If 15% Markup is Eliminated:**
   918	At order line-item entry, labor costs are entered at actual value. No markup is automatically applied. Commission calculations apply commissions to actual costs only. Project GP reflects true profitability without any contingency markup. This requires change communication to sales teams about commission impacts.
   919	
   920	#### Solution Validation
